HEADWORD: Scamillus
<hw>Sca*mil"lus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Scamilli</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., originally, a little
bench, dim. of <ets>scamnum</ets> bench, stool.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A sort of second plinth or block, below the
bases of Ionic and Corinthian columns, generally without moldings, and
of smaller size horizontally than the pedestal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scammoniate</ent>⟦br⟧
